news.title: Home minister distributes sanction letters to 20 lakh PMAY beneficiaries
news.para: Hailing Prime Minister Narendra Modi, he said the second phase of PMAY was approved in the first cabinet meeting after the NDA government came to power for a third consecutive term.

news.title: Two FIRs for cheating filed against Chandigarh-based builder
news.para: The complainants, Vikrant Gupta, Raghawendra, Manju Rani, and Pankaj Arora, alleged that the builder cheated them of Rs 1.1 crore on the pretext of making an investment in a project.

news.title: Land reform law is step taken towards innovation: Uttarakhand CM
news.para: The Uttarakhand Assembly on Friday passed the Uttarakhand (Uttar Pradesh Zamindari Destruction and Land Reforms Act, 1950) (Amendment) Bill, 2025.

news.title: Signature Global expects operational revenue set to cross Rs 3,000 crore in FY26
news.para: "The company's performance in the first three quarters of this fiscal has been very strong across all major parameters like sales bookings, launches, collection from customers and deliveries," Aggarwal said.

news.title: Chandigarh: CHB starts demand survey for sector 53 self-financing housing scheme
news.para: The scheme will tentatively have three categories of flats, including sub-scheme A - HIG (192 units); sub-scheme B - MIG (100 units); and sub-scheme C - EWS (80 units).

news.title: Property-tax offices to remain open on Saturdays till March 31: Delhi civic body
news.para: In a move to facilitate property-tax payments, the offices will remain open from 10 am till 5 pm, providing additional convenience to taxpayers.

news.title: Hong Kong: New World Development sees loss of up to $875 million in H1 2025
news.para: China's property sector has been battling declining demand, with official data on Wednesday indicating that new home prices stalled in January despite continued government efforts to prop up sentiment.

news.title: Goa government forms panel to assess Moti Dongor slum rehabilitation
news.para: The committee, to be chaired by the director of municipal administration, brings together key officials from various departments to develop a comprehensive rehabilitation plan.

news.title: Bidhannagar civic body ropes in women from SHGs for door-to-door property tax collection
news.para: The Bidhannagar Municipal Corporation (BMC) is engaging women from self-help groups for door-to-door property tax collection in Salt Lake and Rajarhat-Gopalpur. These women will assist taxpayers in paying their bills on the spot through an app and collect dues, raising the tax collection target to Rs 44 crore.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh allocates Rs 25,000 crore for urban development
news.para: Urban development minister AK Sharma said, "With this budget, UP would get state-of-the-art building structures, international shooting range and better infrastructure in the cities. The govt is going to enhance the liveability of the cities."

news.title: Telangana amends property registration rules, to allow concessions for illegal layouts
news.para: The municipal administration department issued a GO on Thursday to amend the Telangana Regularisation of Unapproved and Illegal Layout Rules, 2020.

news.title: Hyderabad: GHMC seals Taj Banjara hotel over property tax dues; partial payment made
news.para: The hotel, which has not been operational for the past two years, saw immediate action from its owners after the sealing.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad budget 2025 proposes no property tax hike
news.para: According to Singh, PCMC has decided to use around 10% of the property tax collected from a particular zone on infrastructure projects executed in that zone.

news.title: Telangana government to bring affordable housing policy soon for LIG & MIG
news.para: As part of the plan, the govt has made the Telangana Housing Board (THB) as the nodal agency for implementing the ‘affordable housing policy'.

news.title: CorporatEdge to invest Rs 100 crore in Bengaluru over the next three years
news.para: ​CorporatEdge is looking to add six new centers, having 200,000 sq ft of workspace with over 2,400 seats capacity.

news.title: Nagpur civic body approves 296 high-rise building plans in FY25
news.para: The surge in vertical construction is reshaping the city's skyline, driven by urban expansion, redevelopment projects, and increased housing demand.

news.title: Over 19,000 beneficiaries in Nagpur district to get PMAY homes on Feb 22
news.para: The official sanction and initial instalment of funds shall be disbursed in a ceremony on Saturday presided over by Union home minister Amit Shah, chief minister Devendra Fadnavis, and rural development minister Jaykumar Gore on a virtual platform.

news.title: Karnataka RERA fails to recover Rs 666 crore from builders
news.para: As on Dec 31, 2024, K-Rera had issued recovery orders worth Rs 758 crore against 278 builders in cases filed by 1,660 homebuyers since 2017. But it had recovered only Rs 92 crore, according to official data.
